notesStmt.note: Juz' divisions were added at a later date. Owner's notes and inscriptions dated 1223, 1231, 1250, 1252, and 1260, as well as an undated seal.

msIdentifier.repository: Burke Library at Union Theological Seminary

msContents.summary: Complete copy of the Qurʼān, the first leaf is likely a later replacement; several owners notes.

author.name: Arabic Manuscripts Collection (Burke Library at Union Theological Seminary)

supportDesc.extent: i, 110, i foliated leaves : 138 x 94 (113 x 61) mm, bound to 138 x 100 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Gilt frame with scrollwork lined in black (f. 2r), finispieces in gold and red with braid frame (f. 109v-110r); gold marginal medallions with red, black, or blue centers mark text divisions, sūrah titles in gold lined in black; vocalizations and readings in red and green.
Example of marginal medallion in black
Example of marginal medallion in red
Example of marginal medallion in blue

binding.p: Bound in red-brown leather over pasteboard with flap; blind-stamped central mandorla with four blind-tooled lines extending in the cardinal directions and a blind-tooled frame; coordinating stamp on the flap; yellow paper doublure.

origin.p: Item is not dated, perhaps copied in the 14th or 15th century?
